content:
You can add custom functions for use in formulas using Apex.

In Vlocity Health and Insurance Spring '21 and later releases, you can use the FUNCTION function instead.

Create the Apex Code for the Custom Function.
Define the Metadata for the Custom Function.
Handle any LIST input.
Test the Custom Function.

To implement a custom function, define an Apex class and add a method to the class that contains the function logic.
An Apex class implements methods for three custom functions in OmniStudio, which Integration Procedures and Omnistudio Data Mappers can use. These functions convert a list to an array, replace one character with another, and reformat phone numbers.

Define the metadata required for a custom function in Salesforce.
If an input to your custom function is of the type List<Object>, the input is saved to a VLOCITY-FORMULA-LIST key.
To verify that you have configured the custom function correctly, go to the Omnistudio Data Mapper Designer Formula tab, add a formula, and type the first letter of the function name.
title: Creating Custom Functions in OmniStudio
